# Standalone TIFF-import voxel/ISTHMUS recession example.
# The committed TIFF is a small carbon-sample crop converted to ISTHMUS's
# narrow active-value convention: 1 means solid.

units si

voxel material carbon density 1800.0
voxel create solid tiff file examples/tiff-carbon-sample/carbon-sample-top-crop.tif dx 3.3757e-6 material carbon
voxel ghost solid axis y boundary infinite layers 1
voxel ghost solid axis z boundary infinite layers 1

source q1 constant 1800.0 units kg/m2/s
timestep mass/courant 0.5 source q1

stats 1
stats_style step time active-voxels deleted-voxels remaining-mass mass-fraction volume-fraction
voxel dump hist solid history 1 output/tiff-carbon-sample-constant/history.csv
voxel dump vox solid vtu 1 output/tiff-carbon-sample-constant/voxels_*.vtu select active scalar mass-fraction
surface dump skin skin vtp 1 output/tiff-carbon-sample-constant/surface_*.vtp

variable i loop 12
label ablate-loop
isthmus surface skin voxels solid buffer 1 weighting no map yes crop real
surface flux skin source q1 select normal nx -1.0 ny 0.0 nz 0.0 min-cos 0.25
voxel ablate solid surface skin policy local delete yes
run 1
next i
jump SELF ablate-loop
